        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I would have to say if you are not on a PVP server, pack a set of resistance items in one of your bags, and concentrate on HP for your main set-up. Player crafted jewellery is pretty cheap these days, and give a good range of resists. </P><P>When I was about level 45, I tried the same kind of thing. Trying to get HP/INT/MR/FR/CR/PR to a certain level at the same time. Way too hard to do. Until you start getting the very high end items of the game, items that have a balance of all of the stats are pretty few and far between. </P><P>Go for a spare resist set and concentrate your main gear on HP and INT (more emphasis HP then INT mind you). </P><P>For example run to Guk. Get a Platinum Tiara (3AC, 35HP, 50Mana) and put it on your head. Then get a Froggie crown (12AC, 20FR, 20CR) and throw it in your resist pack. Search the world over for anything doable at level 47 for any single head item that gives those combination of stats and you will be searching for a long time. </P><P>Wear the tiara, and when one of your mage/wizzie/druid friends wants to duel, whip out your froggie crown.</P><P>Cheers,<BR>Ancagalon the Black<BR>Warlock - Terris Thule</P><P></P><P>Edited by - Ancagalon on 06/03/2002  17:29:15<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
